WEBVTT

00:04.538 --> 00:06.974
Hey. They got
a new kind of grape.

00:07.007 --> 00:09.710
Says it tastes
just like cotton candy.

00:11.579 --> 00:13.381
Mmm!

00:13.414 --> 00:16.016
That would make a
fantastic wine.

00:16.050 --> 00:17.885
Kids would love it.

00:17.918 --> 00:18.986
Hey, Virginia.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.154
I don't want
to ruin your day,

00:20.188 --> 00:21.889
but your dad's back in town.

00:21.922 --> 00:23.924
What? Ugh!
That sucks.

00:23.957 --> 00:26.260
And I was so excited
about the grape thing.

00:26.294 --> 00:28.496
Life's a roller coaster.

00:28.529 --> 00:30.198
JIMMY: Recently, Mom found out
that her dad took off

00:30.231 --> 00:32.266
when she was little,
because he was a gay man

00:32.300 --> 00:34.535
living in a small-minded town.

00:34.568 --> 00:37.871
She also learned he had
secretly watched her grow up.

00:37.905 --> 00:41.242
Daddy!
But after reuniting, she found
out something else about him:

00:41.275 --> 00:42.943
he's a jerk.

00:42.976 --> 00:45.513
Forgive me for trying
to raise you to a higher level.

00:45.546 --> 00:46.714
I think you should leave.

00:46.747 --> 00:48.182
Good-bye forever.

00:48.216 --> 00:49.717
And since that day,

00:49.750 --> 00:51.919
my mom's wanted nothing
to do with him.

00:51.952 --> 00:53.721
He's been in here all morning
doing dramatic readings

00:53.754 --> 00:55.289
of the Father's Day cards.

00:55.323 --> 00:58.226
"Have an udder-ly fabulous
Father's Day."

00:58.259 --> 00:59.593
And then, see,

00:59.627 --> 01:01.729
it has a picture
of the aforementioned cow.

01:01.762 --> 01:02.896
Can you see that?

01:02.930 --> 01:04.565
And then, look what he's doing.

01:04.598 --> 01:06.767
He's playing... he's playing
ball with a smaller cow.

01:06.800 --> 01:08.536
Touching, right?

01:08.569 --> 01:10.204
Well, he should read
the sympathy cards

01:10.238 --> 01:12.406
because our
relationship is dead.

01:12.440 --> 01:14.142
Maybe we should talk to him.
(groans)

01:14.175 --> 01:16.043
We know what it's like
to have an ungrateful child.

01:16.076 --> 01:17.711
And an uncoordinated child.

01:17.745 --> 01:20.414
And an underachieving child.
But we stuck around.

01:20.448 --> 01:22.216
Hey, Mom. I'm right here.

01:22.250 --> 01:23.817
And a child
with an annoying voice.

01:23.851 --> 01:25.419
BARNEY (over P.A.):
Attention, Howdy's shoppers,

01:25.453 --> 01:26.920
I have two announcements.

01:26.954 --> 01:29.290
One, I have
a lost daddy up here

01:29.323 --> 01:31.058
looking for his family.

01:31.091 --> 01:34.762
And, two, I need a price check
on how to forgive your father.

01:34.795 --> 01:36.730
Forget it! I already
forgave him once

01:36.764 --> 01:38.966
and he burned all of us.
We don't need him.

01:38.999 --> 01:40.768
Love your dad.

01:40.801 --> 01:42.470
Love your dad.

01:42.503 --> 01:44.605
Love your dad.

01:44.638 --> 01:46.507
PATRONS:
Love your dad.

01:46.540 --> 01:50.444
ALL (chanting):
Love your dad. Love your dad.

01:50.478 --> 01:51.979
Love your dad.

01:52.012 --> 01:53.614
All right, fine!

01:53.647 --> 01:55.249
I'll talk to him.

01:55.283 --> 01:57.485
Yes!
(applause)

01:57.518 --> 01:59.187
Got your price check, Barney.

01:59.220 --> 02:01.822
How to Forgive Your Father
by Deborah Hitler.

02:01.855 --> 02:04.458
It's on sale for $7.99.

02:05.326 --> 02:07.195
Whoo!

02:07.228 --> 02:08.662
* Here we go

02:08.696 --> 02:11.999
* Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh!

02:12.032 --> 02:14.168
(chanting softly)

02:17.671 --> 02:19.807
(chanting)

02:21.742 --> 02:24.144
Ethnomusicologists sure know
how to apologize.

02:24.178 --> 02:25.679
I'm sorry. It's this way.

02:25.713 --> 02:28.316
(chanting)

02:30.518 --> 02:33.521
This is called
the Toltec Apology Dance.

02:33.554 --> 02:35.623
What I'm trying to do
in these moves, you see,

02:35.656 --> 02:36.724
this is change.

02:36.757 --> 02:39.493
I'm changing.

02:39.527 --> 02:40.828
And this is love.

02:40.861 --> 02:42.363
I'm in love.

02:42.396 --> 02:43.897
Right. With yourself.

02:43.931 --> 02:45.032
'Cause you're
a "narpolist..."

02:45.065 --> 02:46.066
narcolippt...

02:46.099 --> 02:47.067
nars...

02:47.100 --> 02:48.869
Narcissist, Jimmy.
(groans)

02:48.902 --> 02:51.572
I hate it when people try to use
words they can't pronounce.

02:51.605 --> 02:53.006
I've met someone.

02:53.040 --> 02:56.043
I've met someone even more
special than myself.

02:56.076 --> 02:58.479
His name is Oliver and we're
gonna get married and I want...

02:58.512 --> 03:00.548
I want you very much,
all of you,

03:00.581 --> 03:03.417
to attend, especially since I
told him I'm gonna have a big

03:03.451 --> 03:06.520
hometown wedding and that you...
you are actually planning it.

03:06.554 --> 03:07.588
What?

03:07.621 --> 03:08.556
Well, I... I don't know

03:08.589 --> 03:09.590
how to plan a wedding.

03:09.623 --> 03:11.191
I never thought I'd need to.

03:11.225 --> 03:13.327
The Supreme Court
really screwed me.

03:13.361 --> 03:16.564
Sorry, but there is nothing
in this world

03:16.597 --> 03:18.532
that could get me to do that.

03:18.566 --> 03:20.901
How 'bout if I were to pay
for Hope's college education?

03:20.934 --> 03:22.536
Nice try.

03:22.570 --> 03:24.071
Still no.

03:24.104 --> 03:27.908
Would you excuse us
for a moment?

03:27.941 --> 03:29.610
Come on, Mom.

03:29.643 --> 03:31.545
This could change Hope's future.

03:31.579 --> 03:33.213
They make a good point,
Virginia.

03:33.247 --> 03:34.615
Let's go tell Arnold we're in.

03:34.648 --> 03:36.116
No way. He's just trying
to manipulate us

03:36.149 --> 03:37.718
into getting something he wants.

03:37.751 --> 03:39.420
You can't argue with that,
Jimmy.

03:39.453 --> 03:41.689
Your mom knows her absent
father as well as any of us.

03:41.722 --> 03:43.190
We're not doing this.
Case closed.

03:43.223 --> 03:44.858
Hope needs to go to college.
Look, she needs

03:44.892 --> 03:47.895
to expand her horizons and
start thinking for herself

03:47.928 --> 03:49.430
and not just become somebody
who agrees

03:49.463 --> 03:50.798
with the last thing she heard.

03:50.831 --> 03:52.065
Sabrina's right.

03:52.099 --> 03:53.601
Hope should learn to
think for herself,

03:53.634 --> 03:54.735
not just become someone
who agrees

03:54.768 --> 03:55.936
with the last thing she heard.

03:55.969 --> 03:57.104
MAW MAW: Arnold...
(racks shotgun)

03:57.137 --> 03:59.139
...get the hell off my lawn!

03:59.172 --> 04:01.074
Maw Maw,
put the gun down.

04:01.108 --> 04:02.310
Don't worry, Arnold.

04:02.343 --> 04:03.777
We had the firing pin
removed after

04:03.811 --> 04:05.713
the piÃ±ata incident at
Hope's birthday party.

04:05.746 --> 04:07.114
Got my eyes on you, mister.

04:07.147 --> 04:08.081
Everything is

04:08.115 --> 04:09.082
milky and blurred,

04:09.116 --> 04:11.084
but I can make out shapes,

04:11.118 --> 04:13.053
and yours is shifty.

04:13.086 --> 04:15.723
I agree. And as much as I'd like
to believe that he'll pay

04:15.756 --> 04:18.292
for Hope's college, I kind of
wish we'd let Maw Maw shoot him.

04:18.326 --> 04:19.427
You know, I'm serious
about this,

04:19.460 --> 04:20.794
and I'll put it in writing.

04:20.828 --> 04:22.095
You know a good lawyer?

04:22.129 --> 04:23.397
We know a lawyer.

04:23.431 --> 04:25.499
And that's how I got
the nickname

04:25.533 --> 04:27.901
Wally "Chocolate Thunder"
Phipps.

04:27.935 --> 04:29.637
JIMMY:
Well, thanks again
for coming straight

04:29.670 --> 04:32.440
from your basketball game to
write up this contract, Wally.

04:32.473 --> 04:33.574
Luckily for you,

04:33.607 --> 04:35.443
I always keep a boilerplate

04:35.476 --> 04:38.846
marine vessel purchase contract
in my gym bag.

04:38.879 --> 04:41.482
So, we plan a great
wedding for him

04:41.515 --> 04:43.951
and he pays for
Hope's college.
Yep.

04:43.984 --> 04:46.119
You'll see in paragraph 12,

04:46.153 --> 04:50.524
right after the section
on international waters,

04:50.558 --> 04:53.794
the provision clearly states...

04:53.827 --> 04:55.195
Damn!

04:55.228 --> 04:56.764
I gotta get
the prescription

04:56.797 --> 04:58.766
on these rec specs checked.
Uh...

04:58.799 --> 05:01.635
"all parties agree that if said
wedding should prove seaworthy

05:01.669 --> 05:04.037
"and payment is not made,
party A

05:04.071 --> 05:05.873
"will surrender his deed
to his fabulous

05:05.906 --> 05:08.509
"Sedona condominium
to party B

05:08.542 --> 05:11.278
to cover college expenses
and docking fees."

05:11.311 --> 05:13.313
Ironclad.

05:13.347 --> 05:14.815
This is amazing.

05:14.848 --> 05:17.117
Hope's gonna be the first
Chance to go to college.

05:17.150 --> 05:19.553
Yeah. And she'll have the money
to afford a good one, too.

05:19.587 --> 05:21.154
Nothing with the words
"Tech," "State"

05:21.188 --> 05:22.956
or "Arizona" in the name.

05:22.990 --> 05:24.825
All right. We got to get going.
We have a wedding in three days.

05:24.858 --> 05:27.661
Three days?
What? We can't plan
this in three days.

05:27.695 --> 05:28.862
Well, you're gonna have to.

05:28.896 --> 05:30.531
Oliver's gonna be here
in three days.

05:30.564 --> 05:32.065
Wait, where does
it say that?

05:32.099 --> 05:34.402
What did you think it meant
when you agreed that

05:34.435 --> 05:39.039
"transaction must be completed
in less than 96 bells"?

05:40.841 --> 05:43.677
You people either need
to brush up on your maritime law

05:43.711 --> 05:46.013
or find a real lawyer.

05:52.553 --> 05:54.254
Ugh.
Where the hell is it?

05:54.287 --> 05:56.890
This is terrible. Hope's never
gonna go to college.

05:56.924 --> 05:59.226
We don't know anything
about planning a wedding.

05:59.259 --> 06:00.928
Oh, I can pull
off a wedding.

06:00.961 --> 06:03.063
I've been planning this
since I was a little girl.

06:03.096 --> 06:04.598
You've been planning
your estranged gay father's

06:04.632 --> 06:06.366
backyard wedding
since you were a little girl?

06:06.400 --> 06:09.737
No. I've been planning
a wedding fit for a princess,

06:09.770 --> 06:11.439
which is close enough.

06:11.472 --> 06:15.709
Wow. Wedding Extravaganza
Dream Book.

06:17.945 --> 06:19.913
We got three days,
Arnold's credit card

06:19.947 --> 06:22.115
and a dream wedding planned
by an eight-year-old.

06:22.149 --> 06:24.452
What could possibly go wrong?

06:27.421 --> 06:29.423
(bell dings)

06:30.624 --> 06:32.726
I've come here
because I've heard

06:32.760 --> 06:34.962
you are a professional stalker.

06:34.995 --> 06:37.431
I said
I'm a professional stocker.

06:37.465 --> 06:39.533
As in, I stock shelves.

06:39.567 --> 06:41.034
Also,

06:41.068 --> 06:44.972
I do spy on people so...
continue.

06:45.005 --> 06:47.808
Arnold, Virginia's dad,
is up to no good,

06:47.841 --> 06:52.546
and it's up to us to expose him
before it's too late.

06:52.580 --> 06:53.714
I'm in, Barbara June,

06:53.747 --> 06:55.483
mostly 'cause I
want an answer

06:55.516 --> 06:59.152
to the "will they or won't they"
that is our relationship.

07:03.123 --> 07:04.958
JIMMY:
With only three days
until Oliver arrived,

07:04.992 --> 07:07.394
the Wedding Extravaganza
Dream Book that Mom made

07:07.427 --> 07:10.230
as a little girl was going
to be Hope's ticket to college.

07:10.263 --> 07:12.466
(groans)
You guys.

07:12.500 --> 07:15.669
You just find a dead possum
in here, you don't pick it up?

07:15.703 --> 07:17.170
Come on!

07:17.204 --> 07:20.440
(possum chattering)
Oh, God. Not dead. Not dead!

07:20.474 --> 07:22.743
That's fantastic.
You have amazing taste.

07:22.776 --> 07:24.177
Really?
Mm-hmm.

07:24.211 --> 07:26.313
I was worried
you'd think it was tacky.

07:26.346 --> 07:27.748
How you gonna get Kenny Loggins?

07:27.781 --> 07:29.683
Oh, we won't.
But luckily Natesville has

07:29.717 --> 07:31.952
the most Kenny Loggins
impersonators per capita

07:31.985 --> 07:33.253
of any other 27-square-mile

07:33.286 --> 07:35.523
unincorporated township
in America.

07:35.556 --> 07:37.791
(Kenny Loggins' "Footloose"
begins)

07:44.632 --> 07:46.800
We've been slacking off
for four years,

07:46.834 --> 07:48.502
but now that we know
you're gonna have the money
to get to college,

07:48.536 --> 07:51.605
it's time for all
of us to get serious.

07:51.639 --> 07:54.141
Let's get you up
to your college height.

07:57.645 --> 07:59.379
Shoot.

08:00.380 --> 08:03.050
* Been working so hard

08:03.083 --> 08:05.152
* I'm punching my card

08:05.185 --> 08:07.287
* Eight hours...

08:07.320 --> 08:09.189
Okay. Hold real still.

08:10.524 --> 08:11.792
Smile.

08:11.825 --> 08:14.995
Congratulations,
Claudia Rosenbaum.

08:15.028 --> 08:17.497
* Holding me down...

08:20.367 --> 08:22.135
Is this really necessary?

08:22.169 --> 08:23.971
We have to make sure it's safe
for the guests at the wedding.

08:24.004 --> 08:25.038
What if it's not?

08:25.072 --> 08:27.675
Then we'll know.

08:31.712 --> 08:34.014
* Tonight I got to cut loose

08:34.047 --> 08:35.515
* Footloose...

08:35.549 --> 08:37.317
The key to surviving
a college food fight

08:37.350 --> 08:39.687
is to have ammo that can't
be thrown back at you

08:39.720 --> 08:41.488
and good aim.

08:41.521 --> 08:43.691
Here we go.

08:46.026 --> 08:47.394
Pretty good.

08:47.427 --> 08:50.898
Got to get a little
windup in, like this.

08:52.032 --> 08:53.366
Fling it.

08:54.935 --> 08:56.704
Yeah!

08:57.237 --> 08:58.772
Backhand.

09:00.407 --> 09:02.542
* Jack, turnin' it loose

09:02.576 --> 09:04.344
* Footloose

