09:24.598 --> 09:26.566
Thank you.

09:26.600 --> 09:29.069
What is this?

09:29.102 --> 09:30.070
Oh, this.

09:30.103 --> 09:31.872
This is
Oliver's harp.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.708
He just wants to play something
at the... at the wedding.

09:34.742 --> 09:36.409
He's a very good
hip-hop harpist.

09:36.443 --> 09:37.711
Mm.

09:37.745 --> 09:38.779
Hey, guys,

09:38.812 --> 09:39.780
Hope's all ready for college.

09:39.813 --> 09:40.948
Check out what she can do.

09:40.981 --> 09:42.616
Throw your hat.

09:43.617 --> 09:45.252
Huh?

09:45.786 --> 09:47.254
(chuckles)

09:47.287 --> 09:48.756
She can't make it freeze
in the air yet,

09:48.789 --> 09:50.223
but we got plenty of time.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.459
It's like seeing 18 years
into the future.

09:52.492 --> 09:54.762
You know, I know, um,
you're only doing this

09:54.795 --> 09:56.396
because I bribed you.

09:56.429 --> 09:59.933
But I got to tell you,
I am so touched.

09:59.967 --> 10:04.104
And I-I'm having so much
fun with you, honey.

10:04.137 --> 10:06.139
I've had fun, too.

10:06.173 --> 10:09.576
I guess you really have changed.

10:09.609 --> 10:12.512
Get your hands
off my granddaughter!

10:12.545 --> 10:14.614
That man is a lying sack
of garbage.

10:14.648 --> 10:16.616
And we've got the proof.

10:18.652 --> 10:20.587
By the way, I'm Frank.

10:20.620 --> 10:22.823
We met briefly,
last time you were here.

10:22.856 --> 10:24.591
Oh, yes, I remember.
Hi, Frank.

10:24.624 --> 10:26.326
Pleasure.

10:30.563 --> 10:32.299
As you will see from
this footage, Arnold is

10:32.332 --> 10:34.034
a lying,
manipulative,

10:34.067 --> 10:35.635
deceitful monster.

10:35.669 --> 10:37.637
ARNOLD (on video): Yeah, yeah.
(chuckles)

10:37.671 --> 10:38.872
Uh-huh.

10:38.906 --> 10:41.441
No, no.
It's-it's going perfectly.

10:41.474 --> 10:43.310
They have no idea
that the wedding is fake

10:43.343 --> 10:45.112
and that Oliver doesn't exist.

10:45.145 --> 10:46.880
I said

10:46.914 --> 10:48.982
(loudly):
Oliver does not ex...

10:49.016 --> 10:51.518
Forget it. I'll text you.

10:51.551 --> 10:54.487
One lousy cell tower
for the whole town.

10:54.521 --> 10:55.789
Is this true?

10:55.823 --> 10:57.390
Were you lying?

10:57.424 --> 11:00.460
Well, I guess, uh, it's time
for me to expose myself.

11:00.493 --> 11:01.862
Oh, God.

11:01.895 --> 11:04.798
Physically, I've always been
about an eight,

11:04.832 --> 11:07.500
but, um...
as a father, I've...

11:07.534 --> 11:09.502
I've been a zero.
I wasn't there for you.

11:09.536 --> 11:11.171
I certainly wasn't
there to throw you

11:11.204 --> 11:13.040
the wedding of your dreams.

11:13.073 --> 11:14.808
Because if I had been,

11:14.842 --> 11:16.509
it would have been just like

11:16.543 --> 11:19.146
the wedding you're planning
for tomorrow...

11:19.179 --> 11:21.148
because this wedding

11:21.181 --> 11:22.382
is for you.

11:22.415 --> 11:23.884
Oh, sure it is.

11:23.917 --> 11:25.385
You know what?
You're just trying...

11:25.418 --> 11:28.388
And this... is for you.

11:28.421 --> 11:31.691
Oh, my God... (gasps)

11:36.396 --> 11:38.531
It's Princess Diana's dress.

11:38.565 --> 11:39.699
(gasps)

11:39.733 --> 11:41.568
How did you know?

11:41.601 --> 11:43.503
ARNOLD:
Just because I wasn't
part of your life,

11:43.536 --> 11:45.705
doesn't mean I didn't keep you
as a part of mine.

11:45.739 --> 11:47.607
I saw you watch
the royal wedding.

11:47.640 --> 11:49.943
Often, when I came
into town to spy on you

11:49.977 --> 11:51.745
like a loving father,
you would be working

11:51.779 --> 11:54.214
on that scrapbook
and watching that videotape.

11:54.247 --> 11:56.416
Until one day you weren't.

12:03.556 --> 12:05.058
When I saw you
give up your dream,

12:05.092 --> 12:06.559
it broke my heart.

12:06.593 --> 12:08.261
I have always loved you...

12:08.295 --> 12:10.563
Oh...
...and you've always
loved the dress.

12:12.465 --> 12:13.901
Burt...

12:13.934 --> 12:15.102
(sniffs)

12:15.135 --> 12:17.270
...we're gonna have a wedding.

12:19.907 --> 12:22.242
ARNOLD:
Oh, my, my, my, my.

12:22.275 --> 12:24.611
There's
my princess.

12:24.644 --> 12:25.779
Here you go, pretty.

12:25.813 --> 12:28.081
You ready?
Yeah.

12:30.650 --> 12:32.452
JIMMY: Mom finally got
the royal wedding

12:32.485 --> 12:34.087
she had always dreamed of.

12:34.121 --> 12:36.456
*

12:36.489 --> 12:37.891
And it even came with a replica

12:37.925 --> 12:39.893
of Princess Diana's
25-foot train--

12:39.927 --> 12:41.929
a train that Hope
would eventually ride

12:41.962 --> 12:43.931
all the way to college.

