13:08.822 --> 13:10.157
"and Mark moved,

13:10.190 --> 13:12.425
"I realize I know

13:12.459 --> 13:13.927
you're the one, forever."

13:13.961 --> 13:16.163
(guests gasp and murmur
with delight)

13:17.898 --> 13:20.100
"Virginia, you are
the coolest girl

13:20.133 --> 13:21.368
"I've ever known.

13:21.401 --> 13:23.436
"If anyone ever
hurts you,

13:23.470 --> 13:25.973
I'll punch them in the face."

13:26.006 --> 13:27.340
Still holds.

13:28.641 --> 13:31.778
Now by the power
vested in me by no one--

13:31.811 --> 13:33.680
uh, because this is

13:33.713 --> 13:36.149
my Halloween costume
from three years ago--

13:36.183 --> 13:37.150
(guests chuckle)

13:37.184 --> 13:38.785
I now pronounce you:

13:38.818 --> 13:41.188
still man and wife.

13:42.522 --> 13:45.525
(cheering)

13:52.699 --> 13:54.868
(cannons boom, guests gasp)

14:09.716 --> 14:11.151
It is with great honor

14:11.184 --> 14:12.986
that Jazzoo will now present

14:13.020 --> 14:14.854
Kenny Loggins' classic hit...

14:14.888 --> 14:16.389
Excuse me, guys.

14:16.423 --> 14:19.092
Um... while kazoo is not

14:19.126 --> 14:21.528
the most annoying
instrument in the world--

14:21.561 --> 14:25.165
that, uh, honor goes to
the aboriginal torture flute--

14:25.198 --> 14:28.368
I had something else in mind.

14:30.270 --> 14:31.238
(gasps)

14:31.271 --> 14:32.872
Uh...
is it...
(gasps)

14:32.906 --> 14:34.007
Oh, my God.

14:34.041 --> 14:35.042
We're going to perform

14:35.075 --> 14:36.443
with Kenny Loggins!

14:36.476 --> 14:38.912
Sorry, guys,
I'm kind of a solo act now.

14:38.946 --> 14:40.113
But you don't even have

14:40.147 --> 14:41.748
the classic Loggins
hair and beard.

14:41.781 --> 14:44.084
Uh, that's because
it's not the '80s.

14:44.117 --> 14:46.053
In Natesville,
it's always the '80s.

14:49.256 --> 14:50.790
Holy crap!

14:50.823 --> 14:52.892
Footloose dance party
is actually happening!

14:52.926 --> 14:54.194
Yeah!

14:54.227 --> 14:55.562
Um, maybe in a little bit,

14:55.595 --> 14:57.030
but I got a tip from somebody...

14:57.064 --> 14:58.365
Me, it was me.

14:58.398 --> 15:00.133
...that the bride
and groom might like

15:00.167 --> 15:02.135
another one of my songs
for their first dance.

15:02.169 --> 15:03.603
Play "Fight
This Feeling"!

15:03.636 --> 15:05.905
Uh, I think
that's R.E.O. Speedwagon.

15:05.939 --> 15:07.207
I know.

15:07.240 --> 15:08.708
It's just a simple
chord progression.

15:08.741 --> 15:09.977
Can't you
just play it?

15:12.279 --> 15:14.247
(playing "Danny's Song")

15:19.119 --> 15:21.921
* People smile and tell me

15:21.955 --> 15:24.491
* I'm the lucky one...

15:24.524 --> 15:26.759
JIMMY:
I requested this song

15:26.793 --> 15:28.261
because it reminded me
of the first day

15:28.295 --> 15:29.596
I brought Hope home.

15:29.629 --> 15:32.065
I had no idea what to do.

15:32.099 --> 15:33.766
But when Mom and Dad
sang this song

15:33.800 --> 15:35.568
to get Hope to sleep,

15:35.602 --> 15:38.238
they also gave me my first
lesson in being a parent.

15:38.271 --> 15:41.308
* Conceived in love

15:41.341 --> 15:44.777
* Sun is gonna shine above

15:46.213 --> 15:49.016
* Even though
we ain't got money *

15:49.049 --> 15:52.019
* I'm so in love with you,
honey... *

15:52.052 --> 15:53.520
JIMMY:
Now everything was perfect.

15:53.553 --> 15:55.122
Excuse me...
(clears throat)

15:55.155 --> 15:56.456
May we cut in?

15:56.489 --> 15:58.191
Oh, well...

15:58.225 --> 16:01.194
I would love to dance with
this pretty little college girl.

16:04.297 --> 16:06.599
Thanks, Dad.

16:06.633 --> 16:09.002
This was even better than
I could possibly dream.

16:09.036 --> 16:11.838
I told you I wanted
everything perfect.

16:11.871 --> 16:14.674
I just wish I could've
sent you on your...

16:14.707 --> 16:16.776
your dream honeymoon
from your scrapbook.

16:16.809 --> 16:17.977
That's okay.

16:18.011 --> 16:19.679
I think that cool
murdering whale

16:19.712 --> 16:23.150
got sent to some marine park
in South America, anyway.

16:23.183 --> 16:25.685
(chuckles)

16:25.718 --> 16:27.820
Although...

16:27.854 --> 16:29.556
if you wanted to let us stay

16:29.589 --> 16:32.692
in your condo in Sedona
for a few days...

16:32.725 --> 16:34.461
Yeah. We-we'd love
to drive up there.

16:34.494 --> 16:35.828
Or down there.

16:35.862 --> 16:37.964
Or fly, or sail...

16:37.997 --> 16:40.033
All right, we don't know
where Sedona is.

16:40.067 --> 16:41.801
But we'd still love
to come stay there.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.170
Yeah, that, uh...

16:43.203 --> 16:44.637
that, uh, that would be, uh...

16:44.671 --> 16:45.838
great, at some point.

16:45.872 --> 16:47.640
What do you mean,
"at some point"?

16:47.674 --> 16:49.509
Well...
(clears throat)

16:49.542 --> 16:51.644
...the condo is, uh...

16:51.678 --> 16:55.014
sort of out of my hands,
at this point.

16:55.048 --> 16:57.084
And whose hands would the condo

16:57.117 --> 16:59.686
that's supposed to pay
for Hope's college be in?

16:59.719 --> 17:03.190
The people I sold... it to...

17:03.223 --> 17:04.757
t-to pay for this wedding.

17:04.791 --> 17:07.660
* I'm so in love
with you, honey *

17:07.694 --> 17:09.196
(guests exclaim)
* And everything will bring...

17:09.229 --> 17:10.097
(stops playing)

17:10.130 --> 17:12.565
Sorry. I had to.

17:12.599 --> 17:15.735
I just vowed to punch
anyone who hurt Virginia.

17:20.573 --> 17:22.442
VIRGINIA:
What do you mean you can't
pay for Hope's college?

17:22.475 --> 17:24.377
She was going to be the
first one in our family

17:24.411 --> 17:25.945
who didn't have to scrub
toilets, mow lawns

17:25.978 --> 17:27.380
or bag groceries
for a living.

17:27.414 --> 17:28.881
I fully intend to...

17:28.915 --> 17:31.351
figure out a way to pay
for Hope's education.

17:31.384 --> 17:32.619
I just...
I-I might have to

17:32.652 --> 17:35.855
wait for the
ethnomusicology business

17:35.888 --> 17:37.724
to just perk up just
a little bit, it's...

17:37.757 --> 17:39.025
Maybe it'll be better

17:39.058 --> 17:40.693
if-if we all work
on this together.

17:40.727 --> 17:42.195
You know,
we're her parents.

17:42.229 --> 17:44.764
We can figure out
a way to pay for this,

17:44.797 --> 17:46.899
even if it means
saving $1,000 a year.

17:46.933 --> 17:48.701
That should
cover it, right?

17:48.735 --> 17:50.203
Yeah, if you're talking about
the boob job she'd need

17:50.237 --> 17:51.638
in order to pole-dance
her way through college.

17:51.671 --> 17:54.073
You know, I think
the salient point

17:54.107 --> 17:56.243
was succinctly covered

17:56.276 --> 17:57.577
in Mr. Loggins' refrain:

17:57.610 --> 17:59.879
"Even though we ain't got money,

17:59.912 --> 18:03.583
we are so much in love
with each other, honey."

18:05.118 --> 18:07.887
I packed your crap. (sighs)

18:07.920 --> 18:09.889
You can go.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.058
(laughing)

18:12.091 --> 18:15.595
I... I have no place to go.

18:16.963 --> 18:18.431
(crying)

18:18.465 --> 18:20.300
Arnold can have
my old room.

18:20.333 --> 18:21.334
What?!

18:21.368 --> 18:23.270
You guys said,
just last week,

18:23.303 --> 18:25.238
that room was still mine

18:25.272 --> 18:27.407
if-if things didn't
work out with Sabrina.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.242
Really. Just last week?

18:29.276 --> 18:31.578
It was your anniversary,
the subject came up...

18:31.611 --> 18:33.180
And to be clear,
he had just told us

18:33.213 --> 18:34.614
he was getting you
a box of envelopes.

18:34.647 --> 18:36.283
The first anniversary
is paper.

18:36.316 --> 18:38.285
Uh, not to make this about me,

18:38.318 --> 18:39.419
but, uh,
what Jimmy said

18:39.452 --> 18:40.587
about the, uh, room...

18:40.620 --> 18:41.854
being available...

18:41.888 --> 18:43.656
is that still on the table?
No.

18:43.690 --> 18:45.658
Okay, I just...

18:45.692 --> 18:48.328
Arnold lied to us
and tricked us,

18:48.361 --> 18:50.263
did all that crazy stuff...
but if you think about it,

18:50.297 --> 18:51.964
that's kind of how
our family shows love.

18:51.998 --> 18:54.167
Maybe we ought to
give him a chance.

18:55.335 --> 18:56.669
Having Hope turned me

18:56.703 --> 18:58.004
into a better person.

18:58.037 --> 19:00.507
If you really want him
to be a better father,

19:00.540 --> 19:02.475
you're going to have
to give him a chance

19:02.509 --> 19:04.143
at having a daughter.

19:04.177 --> 19:05.512
Jimmy...

19:05.545 --> 19:07.113
that was really beautiful.

19:07.146 --> 19:08.648
Most of it was from one
of the Father's Day cards

19:08.681 --> 19:09.716
Arnold performed
at Howdy's.

19:09.749 --> 19:11.551
And I did get to punch somebody

19:11.584 --> 19:13.052
to Kenny Loggins' music.

19:13.085 --> 19:14.654
That puts me in
an exclusive club

19:14.687 --> 19:16.022
with Tom Cruise
and Kevin Bacon.

19:17.190 --> 19:19.492
Not to rush your decision,
but, um...

19:19.526 --> 19:20.960
there's an opportunity

19:20.993 --> 19:24.497
for an incredibly sweet
father-daughter moment

19:24.531 --> 19:26.899
dancing to
Kenny Loggins' song.

19:26.933 --> 19:30.002
And we only have Kenny
for two more minutes.

19:30.036 --> 19:31.538
I'm tempted just to kill you,

19:31.571 --> 19:32.872
'cause then
I could use

19:32.905 --> 19:34.874
my Funeral Extravaganza
Dream Book.

19:36.175 --> 19:38.378
But I guess it's easier
just to forgive you.

19:40.012 --> 19:41.214
Oh, baby...

19:44.083 --> 19:45.652
All right, well,

19:45.685 --> 19:47.220
it's been a very
costly 15 minutes

19:47.254 --> 19:49.422
while everyone has been
processing their feelings,

19:49.456 --> 19:51.824
but I'd really like
to finish "Danny's Song."

19:51.858 --> 19:54.561
Uh, if I don't,
it just keeps going around

19:54.594 --> 19:56.529
in my head and drives me crazy.

19:56.563 --> 19:59.499
(playing "Danny's Song")

19:59.532 --> 20:03.903
* People smile and tell me
I'm the lucky one *

20:04.937 --> 20:08.241
* And we've just begun

20:08.275 --> 20:10.443
* Think I'm gonna have a son

20:13.212 --> 20:15.415
* He'll be like she and me

20:15.448 --> 20:18.518
* As free as a dove

20:18.551 --> 20:21.053
* Conceived in love

20:21.087 --> 20:23.923
* Sun is gonna shine above

20:25.992 --> 20:28.795
* Even though
we ain't got money *

20:28.828 --> 20:32.198
* I'm so in love with you,
honey *

20:32.231 --> 20:34.867
* And everything will bring

20:34.901 --> 20:39.772
* A chain of love

20:39.806 --> 20:42.208
* In the morning, when I rise

20:42.241 --> 20:45.945
* You bring a tear of joy
to my eyes *

20:45.978 --> 20:50.750
* And tell me everything

20:50.783 --> 20:53.920
* Is gonna be all right...

20:53.953 --> 20:56.956
JIMMY: Not everybody becomes
a parent at the perfect time.

20:56.989 --> 20:59.459
Some of us do it way too early,

20:59.492 --> 21:01.461
some of us do it way too late.

21:01.494 --> 21:03.463
The important thing is,

21:03.496 --> 21:05.097
when you get the chance,

21:05.131 --> 21:07.099
you make the most of it.

21:07.133 --> 21:09.902
What's that piece of
trash doing here?

21:09.936 --> 21:12.104
Oh...
No, no, no, no, no!

21:12.138 --> 21:14.173
No, no, no, no. Hey...
(anxious laugh)

21:14.206 --> 21:16.175
Is this going be happening
every five minutes

21:16.208 --> 21:17.977
after she leaves the room?

21:18.010 --> 21:19.946
No, eventually, she'll think
you're her dead husband

21:19.979 --> 21:21.481
and try to make
out with you.

21:21.514 --> 21:22.482
Okay, okay...

21:22.515 --> 21:24.317
How are you?
Good, good.

21:24.351 --> 21:26.419
Good...
I'm good.

21:26.453 --> 21:28.655
I'm good.
(others laughing)

21:32.559 --> 21:35.928
(indistinct talking)
What the hell?

21:35.962 --> 21:37.096
(boat horn honks)

21:37.129 --> 21:38.130
MAN:
Honey, I'm home.
